<br>
There is another way to look at this however.  You can say, well sure I might strike it really rich, and it would be great if nothing was done to my wealth.  But Im here in ths state of nature, I dont know how Im going to do in this system.  What I want is a system that will prehaps not allow as dramatic a success, but will in turn guarentee that I will not absolutely lose.  No matter how poorly things go, I will be provided with the bare necessities of life.  This is the classical game theory response, you maximize your minimum possible gain.<br>
<br>
It's worth nothing that in most random games, for example poker, the classical approach is the most rational way of maximizing long term average wins. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm actually Goanad.</span><br>  Posts: 1051<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/03 5:26:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question for the Libertarians</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> What I want is a system that will prehaps not allow as dramatic a success, but will in turn guarentee that I will not absolutely lose. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I had a longer response typed out but really what this comes down to is understanding that within the opportunity for dramatic success in this &quot;Game&quot; we speak of, is the provision of the correct incentives such that all but the physically\mentally impaired could avoid &quot;absolute loss.&quot; <br>
